<p class="Textbody" dir="ltr" style="margin-left:0.5in;margin-right:0.0in;text-align:justify"><span>Note however that this equation has symmetries which are dubious from a biological viewpoint: the way the population takes off is identical to the way it saturates because the logistic equation has a center of symmetry, </span><span style="font-style:italic">A</span><span> in figure, see also [<a href="#bkmRefNumPara18291924949141">11</a>].</span></p>
